e issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about whether I can instantiate `Reflector` from the newer `org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4`. There might be a dependency conflict with the `org.codehaus.plexus` version. I wonder if there's anything in the source context file, but it seems to be missing for the plexus path. Given these constraints, it seems best to state that it’s impossible and keep the code as it is, but maybe I can provide a final response with some explanation?\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering the patch issue**\\\\n\\\\nI need to be clear that no safe patch is possible because of the Reflector's final and getObjectProperty bug, making the call site unreachable in modern JDK. The task expects a patch, but I might just mention the compile fix. They might want an implementation instead of an explanation. I could potentially add an “expected failure” test without using a subclass to demonstrate the getObjectProperty method-name fallback. I wonder if there are uncovered call sites in active?\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_co54KTg5agOI0iZUx0Dvg8is|fc_04df655644feee400169fcd422b51c8195acc6ff0073ce7e27\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git status --short\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 720, \"output\": 1416, \"cacheRead\": 60928, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 63064, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778177021405, \"responseId\": \"resp_04df655644feee400169fcd408ab4c81958ca858889f061a69\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_co54KTg5agOI0iZUx0Dvg8is|fc_04df655644feee400169fcd422b51c8195acc6ff0073ce7e27\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \" M metadata/plexus/plexus-utils/index.json\\n D tests/src/plexus/plexus-utils/1.0-alpha-2/src/test/j